These are the current steps I have right now for Mac and Windows. Full nodejs scripts at https://github.com/NiceNode/nice-node/tree/feat/podman-runtime/src/main/podman/uninstall. Please let me know if there are any additional files to delete.

Mac
```
const foldersToDelete = [
  '/opt/podman',
  `${userHome}/.local/share/containers`,
  `${userHome}/.config/containers`,
  `${userHome}/.ssh/*podman*`,
  `/private/etc/paths.d/podman-pkg`,
  `/usr/local/podman`,
  `/Library/LaunchDaemons/*podman*`,
];
```
Windows
```
const foldersToDelete = [
  `${userHome}/.local/share/containers`,
  `${userHome}/.config/containers`,
  `${userHome}/.ssh/*podman*`
];
// Equivalent to Windows "Remove program" for currently installed Podman version
const getPodmanAppIdCommand = `Get-WmiObject -Class Win32_Product -Filter "Name LIKE '%Podman%'" | Select-Object -ExpandProperty IdentifyingNumber`;
// parse appId
const uninstallCommand = `msiexec /x ${podmanAppId} /qn`;
